Assemble a Query for an Endpoint

Source: R/query_assemble.R
assemble.Rd

Assemble a Query for an Endpoint

Usage

assemble(obj, qry)

Arguments

obj

An <endpoint>, <collection> or <group> object.

qry

A <query> object.

Value

A list of query parameters matched to an endpoint's fields.

Examples

assemble(
  endpoint("drug_state"),
  query(year = 2022:2024,
  state = any_of("GA", "NY")))
#> https://data.medicaid.gov/api/1/datastore/query/61729e5a-7aa8-448c-8903-ba3e0cd0ea3c/0?count=true&results=true&offset=0&limit=1&conditions[0][property]=state&conditions[0][operator]=in&conditions[0][value][]=GA&conditions[0][value][]=NY
#> https://data.medicaid.gov/api/1/datastore/query/d890d3a9-6b00-43fd-8b31-fcba4c8e2909/0?count=true&results=true&offset=0&limit=1&conditions[0][property]=state&conditions[0][operator]=in&conditions[0][value][]=GA&conditions[0][value][]=NY

assemble(
  endpoint("dial_facility"),
  query(
    state = "GA",
    city = "Atlanta",
    provcity = "Atlanta",
    provider_name = starts_with("C"),
    provname = starts_with("C")
  )
)

assemble(
  endpoint("qppe"),
  query(
    year = 2021:2023,
    practice_state_or_us_territory = any_of("GA", "FL"),
    practice_size = less_than(10, or_equal = TRUE)
  )
)

assemble(
  endpoint("pdc_clinician"),
  query(
    provider_first_name = starts_with("An"),
    provider_last_name = contains("JE"),
    state = any_of("CA", "GA", "NY")))
